STATE OF FLORIDA v SEDORE Case No. 86-163 AC (County Court Case No. 80921, 2NQ) Eleventh Judicial Circuit, Appellate Division, Dade County May 20, 1987 APPEARANCES OF COUNSEL Robert A. Butterworth, Attorney General, and Michael J. Neimand, Assistant Attorney General, for appellant. Robert G. Goberna for appellee.

Before BARAD, DONNER, GREENBAUM, JJ.

OPINION OF THE COURT

PER CURIAM.

The Lower Court dismissed the instant case on the basis that the Traffic Citation did not contain an allegation of venue [i.e. that the charge was committed in the County of Dade] in its body.

We reverse upon the authority of Tucker v. State, 459 So.2d 306 (Fla. 1984).

REVERSED AND REMANDED.
